race.comment: MINER MICK (8) struggled to get involved last start at The Meadows, but prior to that won comfortably by 7 lengths at Warrnambool (25.19) beating Paw Jasta in a Restricted WIN on September 25. Rates on top in this line up. ASTON TRUST (1) is a progressive dog who scored his 2nd career win last time at this track, scoring by 2.5 lengths (31.71). Strong form has emerged from his last run. One of the prime contenders. SHIMA POLLY (5) used the inside to advantage when a maiden winner two back then drew wider last time and could manage only third, beaten 2.5 lengths (25.57) at this track over 450m. Expected to be in the finish again. IVORY MIHARA (2) is a last start winner worth following up.
